content:
Hi,
I saw there is no 'new members' substream. I would like to help with some issues regarding implementation of portable SIMD :) I am quite new to Rust, but I know one or two things about computer architecture. Hope to be of some help here!
Unless you mean for this stream in particular: people are welcome to introduce themselves as they go here! In fact...
Yeah I meant an introduction substeam in here :)
I made an intro in the general one already some time ago

I have dug into several concepts in this group, and I would like to participate some more, do you have any free work that I could help with?
I read through the issues and perused the code. It looks like some implementations of general SIMD operations are required, but I am not sure whether it is still in planning, or are people already working on these issues
@Jakub Duchniewicz Sounds great! I think we have another catch up on Zulip here in about 10ish hours. Maybe we can look at how much we can parallelise right now and work on some contributing docs
I will try to come to the meeting. However AFAIK it is around midnight in my TZ. Nevertheless, I will be tracking everything even if I do not make it :eyes:
